ratings.rComments: I really looked forward to his lectures because he was always so enthusiastic. I think he was a really good professor and presented the material very clearly. If you pay attention in class, do all the homework, and do the mock exams you should do well in the class.
Overcash is an awesome lecturer and I learned a lot of chemistry.  Go to the lectures they are very helpful for understanding the material.
Be prepared for your technique points to be held hostage.
If you show up to his office hours you will have no problem passing this class with a B or higher. By far the best Gen chem teacher
Loved his class! he is nice and welcomes questions especially at office hours

Overcash is actually a great and very funny teacher. He tries to make the class interesting and wants his students to succeed in class. However, his exams are really tough and every question worths lots of points. He is tricky. Be sure to work through all the past exams and mock exams. I would recommend him but prepare to work for the class.

Tests are tough because each question is worth so much and there are only 25 multiple choice question. He tries to trick you. Every point matters - I missed a grade by 6 points. Doable, but I'd rather have taken it with Hummel. Be sure to buy the green book in the bookstore that has the past exams.
He is a really funny guy. His test is not too tough to be finished. But it is still hard to get an A on this course.

Funny guy and great teacher. His lectures were very clear and I hardly did any supplemental learning outside of class. Discussion was useless for the most part. His tests were hard, but fair. Also, I went into the final with a solid B in the class and came out with an A- after lots of studying, so just work hard and you will be fine!
First Midterm and FInal is fairly easy.  Second and third midterm, it's like the opposite.  A great guy though, who gives a really clear lecture!

Some topics were harder to understand because he would skim through them during class, but if you ask him for help, he does a pretty good job explaining them. Tests are honestly not that bad if you listen during lecture and put in the work. Overall, he's a good professor.
He is so smart and awesome tbh

Overcash is an amazing professor! He always make lectures fun to go to and his door is always open to help students out. He knows the material very well and explains it even better. However his class is hard so get ready to read a ton!

Overcash is one of the most dedicated and understanding professors I have ever met. He genuinely cares about each of his students, and he takes the time to get to know those that go to office hours. He tests hardly, but his questions are very fair. I am so grateful to have had him for two separate classes, he is AMAZING!

He lectures well, has office hours, and is available by appointment. He's super enthusiastic and makes general chemistry fun with demonstrations. However, 3 tests and a final are 75% of your grade, quizzes are another 12%, and there is no extra credit. Tests are tricky, often problems not covered in class or hw, but he is by far the best 102 prof.
He's awesome.
Best lecturer I had in UIUC

Dr. Overcash is very helpful! Either you do not understand the lab procedure, or you have some reasons that you cannot attend the lab, just email him or go to his office hours. He explains lab lectures well, but you gotta do the readings beforehand or else you'll be confused.
He's so nerdy and it's adorable.
Going to his office hours once a week is how to survive this class. He's by far the best gen-ed chemistry teacher.

Dr. Overcash is amazing. The first teacher who ever really helped me understand chemistry. Make sure you go to lecture and pay attention. You will learn a lot. Tests are really hard so prepare to really study.

Well organized course. Very test heavy, I believe that three quarters of the points come from the tests. The first two exams are pretty straightforward; not easy, but if you know your stuff you should be fine. Third exam is much more difficult, class average was a shade over 50%. Final isn't too bad. Pretty good professor for gen chem, I'd say.

Chem 102 is going to be challenging no matter what; it's a weed out course. I struggled to get my grade, even after taking AP chem in high school. If chemistry doesn't come easy to you, you're going to need to put effort in.
Not bad at all! Awesome lectures. Exams were tricky, but nothing unfair. Unfortunately, course layout is pretty tight, with little opportunity for extra points or credit.
Great teacher

This is how a class is supposed to be. A professor who absolutely loves the subject and can teach it to you like it's the alphabet. He is fun and hands-on with his teaching. But this class is still tough. Pay attention to him for he will supply you with everything you need, but he will still make you work for the grades. B- class average.

Dr. Overcash explains everything so well but he does go fast during lectures. I suggest you read and do the practice problems that he assigns before lecture. His tests are really hard. He will help you if you reach out to him and go to his office hours.

Overcash was easily the best chem professor, period. He is ready to make you LEARN chemistry and his unique sense of humor makes it much easier. However, his tests could be tricky and I've made my fair share of silly mistakes thanks to them. However, he is definitely willing to give you the A if you work for it. Would have him again for sure!

Overcash's class was hard for me, but for many people he was an easier professor. If you attend lecture and do the worksheets each week even if you don't finish them in discussion, along with the practice tests, you will be okay.
Great professor.

Dr. Overcash's class is flawlessly designed; set up in such a way that if you put in a diligent effort, you'll do very well. Chemistry is by its nature a very difficult class, especially at UIUC, but Overcash's lectures make learning a little easier. Best professor I've had at U of I so far, definitely recommend taking his class.

Chem 102 would have been a terrible class for me without Dr. Overcash's sense of humor and helpfulness outside of lecture. Not many grades other than tests, and they are difficult. Make sure you go to class otherwise you won't understand any of the concepts. Class moves very quickly. If Chem doesn't come easily to you, be prepared to work hard.
Great professor!

I love him. His lectures are amusing and the content is crystal clear. He does fun demos and includes 30 second breaks in every lecture. Super easy on the eyes and has a great personality. The class is hard but if you read the text, study, and go to TA sessions you will pass no problem.
Looks just like John Green, freakin hilarious in class, gives a mid lecture break, TONS OF DEMOS like 2 a class usually.
He tries really hard to get a certain grade distribution and is slightly disappointed when people do better than he thought they would. I enjoy the chemistry memes though.

I find Chemistry to be quite boring, but Dr. Overcash makes engaging, and dare I say, "fun", lectures. He explains topics very well, gives minimal homework, and is a very down to earth guy. Definitely would recommend him.

Overcash is the first professor I had that actually made me WANT to learn. I hate chemistry, but he really cared about my grade as well as how much I was actually learning. I took this class over the summer and I'll say it wasn't easy. But he was always available and cared more than I did at times. Loved him, but makes you work for it!

Dr. Overcast is really young and relatable and overall one of the coolest professors at UIUC. His knowledge of corny jokes is expansive and he knows how hard the class is so he tries his best to bring things down to earth and make it interesting. He cares. I'd recommend him to anyone, and the test curves are out of this world.

Dr. Overcash is the swaggiest teacher in all of Champaign-Urbana. His knowledge of chemistry is only overshadowed by his knowledge of chemistry cat memes. This dude brought sexyback after JT. He is the truth.

Now I really, really...REALLY hate chemistry. however Dr. Overcash made it bareable. he was very nice and very clear on everything he taught and was able to help me with ease when i went to office hours, he was my favorite professor

Great professor who genuinely cares about his students and explains chemical concepts really well. Lectures can get boring sometimes, but the clicker questions in class are very helpful and similar to those on quizzes/exams.

Cares more about your grade then you do. He puts so many resources on his website to help you learn. I hate chemistry but Overcash makes you want to learn and does it in a great way. One of my favorite professors in my least favorite class.

Overcash completely turned around my perception of this class. Made it very interesting, and was extremely helpful and accessible. Plus he had some jokes that were so bad, you had to laugh at them. Kept a very light atmosphere in the class.

Overcash was an average professor. First few exams were straight foward and easy. Third exam (Thermo) he failed to deliver the material correctly. Class average on the exam was 13/25. Final exam was a average in difficulty. Class average was a 60% onthe final. Class was tough but he curved the entire lass 8% or 80 points out of 1000. Don't pick him

He was very hard to understand and read straight from the power points. His quizzes and mock exams were nothing like the real exams. The exams were very confusing and way harder than the mock exams when he said they would be similar. Did not enjoy his class at all.

Dr. Overcash was a great professor. Really cared about the material, had a lot of fun, and was always willing to help. He had to deal with a lot of bull from people in the class who were plain rude or loud in lecture, and did it well. It's a shame that all those people say he was a horrible professor. He definitely taught me chemistry.
He was not very helpful in lecture and mostly just read off the power point slides, which made it difficult to write the lab reports.

Beware, Chem 101 is not an easy class for someone who hates science. Labs, lon-capa, and bookwork will take over your whole week. Tests are pretty complicated and hard to study for. I was able to understand what happened in lecture but I didn't do great on the tests. Discussions didn't help me much either. Take an easier science class if you can.
Best teacher I ever had. Also very young and hot!!!!

Overcash is a really good guy, who you can tell is very passionate about chem. That being said, he isn't the greatest teacher. He was consistently unclear in lecture, not very helpful (when asking for help), and had an obsession with blowing things up (which, while cool, was extremely annoying at 8 in the morning). Basic material, harder tests.

The lectures are extremely boring and it is hard to follow most of the time. He does tons of demos and blows alot of stuff up so if you like that then its a good class but at 8am it was just annoying. I thought the tests were really easy but other people had trouble with them. He isn't that bad though

Overcash is a nice guy who seems to truely love what he is teaching, but he is very inexperienced at being a lecturer. At times he is very hard to follow and I found myself getting lost easily. He blows things up a lot, almost too much. I did not like his class at all and the tests were tricky. But he is a nice guy who loves chemistry.

Overcash is a great teacher who definitely appears to care about whether the students understand what is going on. He show really cool demo's and blows things up a lot which is cool. The class isn't hard which was expected because it is very basic material but the teaching is great although tests may have confusing questions.
Good TA. Grades on time, pretty nice, and explains things clearly. They should hire more TAs like John. As for the course itself...well it was okay...

John is a very good TA for Chemistry 104.  The class is definitely rigorous because Professor Ray covers a lot of material in a short amount of time and relies on the TAs a lot to relay the information to students.  John, however, was one of the better TAs.  He actually held good review sessions and was always there to help if we needed it.
Quality teacher. He got it done for me.
